can better management raise growth and reduce pollution siepr siepr stanford institute for economic policy research search the site enter your keywords main links home about siepr research at siepr centers programs projects education at siepr events at siepr people at siepr publications at siepr economics in the news support siepr contact us stay connected stay connected home research at siepr research project can better management raise growth and reduce pollution title can better management raise growth and reduce pollution principal investigator aprajit mahajan dates august 1 2010 july 31 2012 sponsor sloan foundation abstract in an ongoing field experiment that provides five months of intensive management consultancy to a set of randomly selected large textile firms in india we find that introducing very basic management practices has a large impact on firm productivity for details and references see http www stanford edu nbloom dmm pdf we also noticed that firms had also improved their energy efficiency as a result of the intervention although investigating energy efficiency was not the original purpose of the study the set of effects are becoming clear over time and we are requesting the woods institute for funding to develop the energy focus of the research we propose to use the funding to a collect detailed energy use data on our experimental firms and b introduce a set of energy reduction experiments on firms to explicitly aim to reduce energy use stanford university economics department stanford center for international development public policy program site map economic summit
